<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C17007> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An imaging technique using compounds labelled with short-lived positron-emitting radionuclides (such as carbon-11, nitrogen-13, oxygen-15 and fluorine-18) to measure cell metabolism. It has been useful in the study of soft tissues such as cancer; cardiovascular system; and the brain. SPECT is closely related to PET, but uses isotopes with longer half-lives and resolution is lower." .
<http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/Thesaurus.owl#C17007> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://www.radlex.org/RID/RID10337> .
