<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/NZ9F> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "SavitzkyGolayFilter" .
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/NZ9F> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "This filter is also called also called digital smoothing polynomial filters or least-squares smoothing filter. It is used to \"smooth out\" a noisy signal whose frequency span (without noise) is large. This filter minimizes the least-squares error in fitting a polynomial to frames of noisy data" .
# 
