<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/OKUW> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "This filter applies a Gabor filter with a specified wavelength (in pixels) and orientation (in degrees)" .
# 
# http://www.radiomics.org/RO/OVBL
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/OVBL> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/OVBL> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/TP0I> .
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/OVBL> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "IBSI" .
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/OVBL> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "GLRLM_GreyLevelNonUniformityNormalised" .
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/OVBL> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "This is the normalised version of the grey level non-uniformity feature" .
# 
# http://www.radiomics.org/RO/OWOH
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/OWOH> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/OWOH> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/CINW> .
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/OWOH> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "FeatureSpecificParameters" .
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/OWOH> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Container for parameters and computation methods used to derive features" .
# 
# http://www.radiomics.org/RO/P30P
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/P30P> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/P30P> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/9SAK> .
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/P30P> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "IBSI" .
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/P30P> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "GLSZM_ZonePercentage" .
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/P30P> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "This feature assesses the fraction of the number of realised zones and the maximum num- ber of potential zones. Strongly linear or highly uniform ROI volumes produce a low zone percentage" .
# 
# http://www.radiomics.org/RO/P6QZ
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/P6QZ> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
