<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/YEKZ> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ApproximateVolume" .
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/YEKZ> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "In clinical practice, volumes are commonly determined by counting voxels. For volumes consisting of a large number of voxels (1000s), the differences between approximate volume and mesh-based volume are usually negligible. However for volumes with a low number of voxels (10s to 100s), approximate volume will overestimate volume compared to mesh-based volume. It is therefore only used as a reference feature, and not in the calculation of other morphological features." .
