<http://www.semanticweb.org/ontologies/mCODERadiomics#mCR_0000249> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/ontologies/mCODERadiomics#mCR_0000249> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/ontologies/mCODERadiomics#mCR_0000298> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/ontologies/mCODERadiomics#mCR_0000249> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Genomics Report"@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/ontologies/mCODERadiomics#mCR_0000249> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Structured summary of genomic testing results generated from a molecular diagnostic assay (e.g., NGS panel, whole-exome sequencing)..A genomics report details the analysis of an individual's DNA or RNA, identifying genetic variations and their clinical implications. It typically includes variant classifications, associated gene-disease risks, and personalized treatment or preventative recommendations." .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/ontologies/mCODERadiomics#mCR_0000256
<http://www.semanticweb.org/ontologies/mCODERadiomics#mCR_0000256> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/ontologies/mCODERadiomics#mCR_0000256> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Report"@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/ontologies/mCODERadiomics#mCR_0000256> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An evidence-based document that presents, analyzes, and summarizes medical or scientific data" .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/ontologies/mCODERadiomics#mCR_0000256> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Report" .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/ontologies/mCODERadiomics#mCR_0000261
